{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"celestite-rheophilic-imago","description":"# Completion verifier — coach callers to document completion evidence as ticket comments on any FAIL\n\n## Why\n\nWhen the completion verifier returns FAIL, the only remediation surfaced to the\ncaller is \"address the criteria.\" There is no signposting of the legitimate,\nlow-friction channel for a criterion that is *already satisfied but not\ndiscoverable from the code*: recording the supporting evidence as a comment on\nthe ticket. The completion verifier reads a ticket's comments (via its read-only\n`show_ticket` tool) and the deterministic child-closure gate reads ticket state\ndirectly, so documented evidence is genuinely taken into account on the next run —\nbut nothing tells the caller that. The result is callers reaching for the wrong\nescape hatch instead of the intended evidence channel.\n\n## What\n\nAttach a single, generic remediation-guidance string to **every** FAIL completion\nverdict, at the one chokepoint both failure paths already pass through\n(`reconcile_verdict`), and surface it wherever a FAIL verdict is shown to a caller\n(the close gate and the `verify-completion` text render). The guidance must:\n\n- be generic and broadly applicable (not tied to any one incident);\n- coach the caller to record evidence that meets completion requirements as\n  ticket **comments** (concrete artifacts: file paths + line ranges, commands and\n  their output, links, reasoning connecting the work to the criterion);\n- state that the verifier reads the ticket's comments so documented evidence is\n  incorporated on the next verification;\n- keep the \"finish genuinely incomplete work, then re-verify\" route;\n- NOT mention forcing a ticket closed (steer to the evidence channel only).\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/completion.py` — add a module-level `COMPLETION_REMEDIATION_GUIDANCE`\n  constant (exported) and have `reconcile_verdict` set `result[\"remediation\"]` on\n  any FAIL verdict. Covers both the agentic FAIL and the deterministic\n  child-closure FAIL (`deterministic_child_failure`), which already call\n  `reconcile_verdict`.\n- `src/rebar/schemas/completion_verdict.schema.json` — document the optional\n  `remediation` string field (schema is `additionalProperties: true`, so this is\n  contract documentation, not a breaking change).\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py` — append the verdict's remediation\n  guidance to the blocked-close error, leading with the comments-evidence channel.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py` — render the remediation guidance in\n  `_render_verdict_text` on a FAIL verdict.\n- Tests — assert a FAIL verdict carries `remediation`, that it names the ticket\n  comments channel, and that it does not mention forcing closure.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `reconcile_verdict` sets a non-empty `remediation` string on every FAIL\n      verdict and leaves PASS verdicts without one (no `remediation` on PASS).\n- [ ] The guidance text names the ticket **comments** channel and instructs the\n      caller to document evidence (paths/commands/results/reasoning) that meets the\n      completion requirements; it is generic (no incident-specific wording).\n- [ ] The guidance text does not reference forcing a ticket closed.\n- [ ] A blocked close (`transition <id> in_progress closed` with a FAIL verdict)\n      surfaces the guidance to the caller.\n- [ ] `rebar verify-completion <id>` text output shows the guidance on a FAIL\n      verdict.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass locally; the change lands on\n      `main` through Gerrit with `LLM-Review +1` and `Verified +1`.","id":"19b1-8221-42b7-4381","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Completion verifier: coach callers to document completion evidence as ticket comments on any FAIL"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783686534734156001,"uuid":"2025e702-74fc-4132-8d9f-0e6459def9d3"}